Thanks Margaret and Bruce

  I downloaded the software. I cant seem to find my mic at the moment so I think I am going to just do a few test sessions without recording to make sure my radio is hacked correctly and sweeping the bands. I have it hooked up to the speakers so I can hear if anyone comes through.

  Kay

itcdeadpeople &lt;ITCdeadpeople@...&gt; wrote:
  Hi Kay. All you have to do is plug in an external speaker, setup your computer to record 
(plug in mic, open up software and start recording - I use Audacity) turn on the radio and 
get the scan going, then start talking like you would if you were on the phone to a friend 
(but give a little extra time for them to answer). 

You can open the conversation with something like, &quot;Can you hear me?&quot; or &quot;Can anybody 
use this radio to speak to me?&quot; or you can try asking for someone specific. 

After you are done, close the conversation (again, like you might do if you were on the 
phone wrapping up the conversation with a friend), stop the recording, stop the radio, and 
go back and listen for responses. If you think you hear something &#39;real-time&#39; during your 
session, repeat what you think you heard, so that interaction is recorded. 

Have fun! Margaret

